                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d149">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-02-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 26, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Saw Lord Rosebery to-day. Draft of law to give fall effect to the award and
                    regulations mailed to Sir Julian Pauncefote last Saturday. Lord Rosebery assures
                    intent to execute award without evasion or hesitation. Have sent him note
                    deprecating delay and impressively urging immediate conclusion of the
                    convention.</p>
            </div>
